Remarks. The species can be assigned to the
A. morrisi
group due to having two pairs of spermathecal pores in 5/6/7 and holandry ( Sims & Easton 1972 ). To date, this group comprises 47 species, of which 13 have been recorded in northern and central Vietnam ( Thai 1982 , 1984a ,b; Le 1995 ; Pham 1995 ;
Do et al . 1994
, 1995 ;
Nguyen et al. 2016a
).
